          Variable used to adjust placement of board along the Y-axis.

        • index

          java.util.ArrayList<E> index
          The ArrayList used by the optimizing-function. This is used in order to store information about "active" cells, that is, cells that are alive and/or have neighbors.
          See Also:
          Board.optimaliser, DynamicBoard.updateNeighbourBoard(), DynamicBoard.countNeighbhours(int, int)

        • xmove

          int xmove
          The amount of horizontal movement of a byte[][] to place onto the existing boardArray. Used in order to place a byte[][] at the correct coordinates of the boardArray.
          See Also:
          DynamicBoard.addArrayToBoard(byte[][])

        • ymove

          int ymove
          The amount of vertical movement of a byte[][] to place onto the existing boardArray. Used in order to place a byte[][] at the correct coordinates of the boardArray.
          See Also:
          DynamicBoard.addArrayToBoard(byte[][])

        • topExist

          boolean topExist
          A boolean to determine if there is a topBoard to place.

        • topBoard

          byte[][] topBoard
          The byte[][] representing the pattern to place onto the boardArray.
